.\" MANIFEST: document describing the ``f77'' cookbook
.\"
.H 2 "f77"
This cookbook describes how to work with Fortran files.
.H 3 "recipes"
.VL 1i
.LI "%.o: %.f77"
Construct object files form Fortran source files.
.LE
.H 3 "variables"
.VL 1i
.LI f77
The Fortran compiler command.
Not altered if already defined.
.LI f77_flags
Options to pass to the Fortran compiler command.
Not altered if already defined.
The default is "-O".
.LI f77_src
Fortran source files in the current directory.
.LI dot_src
Source files constructable in the current directory
(unioned with existing setting, if necessary).
.LI dot_obj
Object files constructable in the current directory
(unioned with existing setting, if necessary).
.LI dot_clean
Files which may be removed from the current directory in a clean target.
.LE
.H 3 "See Also"
The ``library'' cookbook, for linking Fortran sources into a library.
.br
The ``program'' cookbook, for linking Fortran sources into a program.
